  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2015-07-15T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Consumer Reporting Fairness Act of 2015\n\nThis bill requires a creditor that has provided or furnished to a consumer reporting agency any item of information pertaining to an account based on a debt discharged in a case under the federal bankruptcy code to inform such agency that the debt has been discharged in bankruptcy and has a zero balance.\n\nAn individual injured by any willful violation of this provision shall recover actual damages, including costs and attorneys' fees, and may recover punitive damages in appropriate circumstances."
  }, 
